value.title: Dr. Nicole Saphier raises concern for Biden pledging a 'draconian' universal mask mandate
value.excerpt: After giving credit to the qualifications of President-elect Joe Biden’s coronavirus advisory board, Fox News medical contributor Nicole Saphier raised a concern about their move to potentially suppress Americans' civil liberties.

value.title: Mike Pence heading to Florida vacation island
value.excerpt: Pence is scheduled to travel to Sanibel, Florida, Tuesday through Saturday, according to the Federal Aviation Administration.

value.title: Trump staffers tweeted an image of a 'President Gore' front page from 2000 to prove the media gets election calls wrong. But the image was fake.
value.excerpt: Trump spokesman Tim Murtaugh said the image showed "the media doesn't select the president." The paper said the image was "doctored."

value.title: Trump cheers Pfizer Inc's experimental COVID-19 vaccine results
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Monday welcomed Pfizer Ic's experimental COVID-19 vaccine results, and the stock market boost it brought.

value.title: Biden coronavirus team to include Rick Bright, ousted HHS official
value.excerpt: Rick Bright, the ousted Health and Human Services official, will be one of 10 advisory board members on Democratic President-elect Joe Biden's coronavirus task force, Biden's transition team announced on Monday.

value.title: Biden plans for White House as Trump plans rallies to protest his election loss
value.excerpt: Democrat Joe Biden won the U.S. presidential election on Saturday after a bitter campaign, sparking street celebrations among his supporters in major cities even as President Donald Trump refused to accept defeat.

value.title: Biden should support push for transparency in vote as ‘ultimate presidential act’: Turley
Trump in denial over election defeat as Biden gears up to fight Covid
value.excerpt: Even with President Donald Trump still refusing to concede the election, President-elect Joe Biden will launch an aggressive plan on Monday to control the pandemic that is escalating at an alarming rate and will define his administration as soon as he takes office.

value.title: Seattle man fatally shot near Biden celebration rally: report
South Dakota Gov. Noem: Al Gore got his day in court -- Trump deserves the same consideration
value.excerpt: South Dakota Gov. Kristi Noem urged the country to “afford the 70.6 million Americans that voted for President Trump the same consideration" provided to former vice president Al Gore in the 2000 legal battle that resulted in a Supreme Court decision and a George W. Bush victory.

value.title: Trump campaign taps Rep. Doug Collins to lead recount team in Georgia
value.excerpt: The recount will begin as soon as canvassing has ended, the campaign said.

value.excerpt: But that alone does not explain why Biden lost the state by about 375,000 votes, a substantial gap in a state known for paper-thin margins. An analysis of post-election data shows that several factors played into the Democrats' bad day.

value.title: New York Gov. Cuomo predicts scientists will speak 'unmuzzled' now that 'Trump is out of office'
value.excerpt: Cuomo said "the political pressure of denying COVID is gone" after Joe Biden's victory was called in the 2020 presidential election.

value.title: Romney says Trump should 'follow every legal option he has,' but choose words 'carefully'
value.excerpt: Sen. Mitt Romney, R-Utah, has no problem with President Trump challenging the 2020 election results in court, but said that he should tone down his public rhetoric.

value.title: Jared Kushner has approached Trump about conceding 2020 election
value.excerpt: Jared Kushner, President Donald Trump's son-in-law and senior adviser, has approached the President about conceding the election, two sources told CNN.

value.title: Buttigieg: Republican Senate would go against 'will of the people' by opposing Biden agenda
value.excerpt: Biden transition team member Pete Buttigieg said Sunday that even if they win enough races to maintain control of the Senate, Republicans would be opposing the will of the American people if they stand in the way of President-elect Joe Biden's agenda.

value.title: After a second loss to Greg Pence, Jeannine Lee Lake sets her sights on 2022
value.excerpt: With 97% of precincts counted in this year's Sixth District Congressional race, Greg Pence had 68.6% of the vote to Jeannine Lee Lake's 27.8%.

value.title: Mary Trump says her uncle, President Trump, will spend the transition period 'breaking stuff' with 'vengeance'
value.excerpt: Trump's niece wrote, in an opinion article for The Observer, that she fears the defeated president will "lash out" after losing the US election.
